Week 5 Summary

- Improved memory extraction so preference statements are saved more reliably (including natural phrasing like "remember that I prefer...").
- Tightened task-note capture so tasks are only saved from explicit task/reminder language, reducing preference-to-task misclassification.
- Added protection against accidental timer/alarm execution when a message is clearly a preference statement.
- Added a new Settings feature toggle for timer/alarm confirmations (similar to open-app confirmation), with backend persistence and API routes.
- Extended confirmable action flow to support timer/alarm set and cancel operations with explicit yes/no confirmation when enabled.
- Added a new Timers & Events dashboard panel in the frontend so users can see active timers/alarms and recently generated calendar actions.
- Wired the Timers & Events dashboard into Quick Access (+ menu) and added Ctrl+Y as a direct shortcut.
- Updated the shortcuts/help panel to include the new Ctrl+Y shortcut.
- Added backend activity logging for calendar create/update/delete actions and exposed dashboard data via a new endpoint.
